<a id="prlead"></a>



<p></p>



<h2>Global Public Relations Lead</h2>



<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>



<p>EARTHDAY.ORG (EDO) is looking for a Global Public Relations Lead to join our growing team. The ideal applicant will possess strong oral and written communications skills, a history of&nbsp;cultivating relationships with influential print, digital and broadcast journalists,&nbsp;and a track record of creating strong campaigns and delivering successful press coverage.</p>



<p>As EDO’s Global Public Relations Lead you will&nbsp;<a>elevate the EARTHDAY.ORG brand and key programs/campaigns year-round. This includes communicating our priorities and program initiatives, and inspiring current and new audiences to engage with and support EARTHDAY.ORG in its mission to diversify, educate, and activate the environmental movement worldwide.&nbsp;</a></p>



<p>The position is based in Washington D.C.&nbsp;</p>



<p><strong>Job Duties</strong></p>



<ul><li>Support the development and execution of multi-channel, integrated communications and engagement strategies on behalf of EARTHDAY.ORG</li><li>On-going cultivation of press relationships (print, broadcast, traditional, environmental-specific) for EDO as a whole and around particular programs/campaigns and executives</li><li>Create, plan and execute tactical communication plans and deliverables to effectively disseminate messages across channels</li><li>Develop and produce documents and public relations materials, including&nbsp;writing and editing press releases and media alerts</li><li>Setting up and assisting with staff press interviews</li><li>Writing and editing occasional website/social content, program reports, and partner/constituent outreach</li><li>Provide support for EDN&#8217;s social media and marketing efforts</li><li>Draft messages on behalf of executive leadership to create and sustain impactful momentum for EDO initiatives</li><li>Maintain global media contact database</li><li>Manage relationships with our vendors related to the development and execution of media outreach</li><li>Track results and media coverage to provide feedback to measure the effectiveness of communications</li><li>Work with the communications staff to create and implement projects and campaigns</li><li>Additional activities in support of the environment</li></ul>



<p><strong>Job Qualifications</strong></p>



<ul><li>Minimum of 3-5 years of related experience and a track record of developing and delivering successful press strategies, outreach, and coverage</li><li>Hold existing&nbsp;relationships with influential print, digital and broadcast journalists</li><li>Knowledge of PR software database tools such as Cision, Muck Rack, Meltwater, PR Newswire or the like</li><li>Strong writing and editing skills, and strong interpersonal skills</li><li>Must be organized, motivated, self-starter</li><li>Interest in environmental issues and the mission of the organization a requirement&nbsp;<strong></strong></li></ul>



<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY</strong></p>



<p>Interested and qualified candidates, please forward a cover letter and resume and a list of professional references to&nbsp;<a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#ff978dbf9a9e8d8b979b9e86d1908d98"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="d1b9a391b4b0a3a5b9b5b0a8ffbea3b6">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>&nbsp;with “Global Public Relations Lead – your full name” in the subject line.&nbsp;</p>



<p><a href="#top">Back to top</a></p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-text-color has-background has-luminous-vivid-amber-background-color has-luminous-vivid-amber-color is-style-wide"/>



<a id="digitalmedia"></a>



<h2>Digital Media Strategist</h2>



<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>



<p>As EDO’s Earth Day Digital Media Associate, principal duties include:    &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<ul><li>Day-to-day support of <a href="http://earthday.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">EARTHDAY.ORG</a>’s social media platforms, including Twitter, Facebook, Instagram, and LinkedIn with unique voices and engagement tailored for each.    &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Develop annual/monthly content and campaign strategy around specific events/monthly themes, writing&nbsp;and content creation, including social media share <strong>graphics</strong>,<strong> video ideation</strong> <strong>and creation</strong>, event photography, and other shareable content to support and complement the priorities of EDO’s strategic communications and editorial calendar.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Analyze data related to digital media campaigns, suggest changes/improvement/new approaches&nbsp;to engage and grow EDO’s digital presence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Responsible for executing all paid media campaigns across digital media platforms including Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and LinkedIn  &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Partner engagement and management – Engagement in partner digital events and activations to grow the network and establish&nbsp;strategic partnership opportunities with partner organizations around the world&nbsp;</li><li>Maintain social media marketing tools to create and maintain the company’s brand&nbsp;</li><li>Analyze the company’s digital marketing plan and social media strategy and identify strategic weaknesses and make recommendations for improvements&nbsp;</li><li>Research social media trends and informing management of changes that are relevant to the company’s marketing activities&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Setting key performance indicators (KPIs) for social media campaigns, such as targets for a certain number of shares or likes and measuring a campaign’s performance against the KPIs&nbsp;</li><li>Live event coverage on social media, as needed &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Work with communications team on a day-to-day basis to develop overall strategy that will contribute to improving the environment, including demonstrating&nbsp;the ability to work individually and as a team player.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>



<p><strong>Other Duties will include:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;</p>



<ul><li>Daily updates to the EDO site to provide&nbsp;content in a clear, consistent, and dynamic way to maximize user experience and engagement &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Help produce Earth Day live&nbsp;webinar&nbsp;series that are generally hosted&nbsp;one to two times a month.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Staff writing&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Special events&nbsp;content creation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Support other staff members (campaign&nbsp;managers) with any content creation needed&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>



<p>Preference Skills:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<ul><li>Excellent writing and communications skills&nbsp;</li><li>Facebook Business Manager and Ads Manager &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Professional and creative copywriting &nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Professional Graphic and video creation&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Adobe illustrator&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Metric tracking and market analysis&nbsp;</li><li>Mission driven&nbsp;</li></ul>



<p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p>



<p>Interested and qualified candidates, please forward a cover letter, including salary requirements, and a resume to: <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#eb8399ab8e8a999f838f8a92c584998c"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="38504a785d594a4c505c594116574a5f">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> with “Digital Media Strategist – ‘your full name’ ” in the subject line.</p>



<p><a href="#top">Back to top</a></p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-text-color has-background has-luminous-vivid-amber-background-color has-luminous-vivid-amber-color is-style-wide"/>



<a id="grantsmanager"></a>



<h2>Grants Manager</h2>



<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>



<p>EARTHDAY.ORG (EDO)is a driving force steering environmental awareness around the world. EDO&#8217;s network reaches over 150,000 partners organizations in 192 countries, coordinating millions of community development and environmental protection activities throughout the year. Our mission is to grow and diversify the environmental movement worldwide, and to mobilize it as the most effective vehicle for promoting a healthy, sustainable planet. We pursue our mission through education, politics, events, and consumer activism.<br><br>As EDN’s Grants Manager your principal duties will include the following:</p>



<ul><li>Conducting the full range of activities required to prepare, submit, and manage grant proposals to foundation and corporate sources;</li><li>Performing prospect research on foundations and corporations to evaluate prospects for corporate and foundation grants;</li><li>Working with program staff to gather information necessary for proposals and reports;</li><li>Work with finance to gather information necessary to report to corporate/foundation funders on current grant programs;&nbsp;</li><li>Comply with all grants reporting as required by foundation/corporate donors;&nbsp;</li><li>Provide stewardship to current donors, including providing regular written updates to corporate and foundation donors;</li><li>Understand institutional history and programs;</li><li>Make appointments for senior management with foundation officers and other prospects;</li><li>Maintain grant tracking and reporting information in the organization&#8217;s database and paper files;</li><li>Track statistics relevant to development; and</li><li>Coordinate preparation and planning for donor presentations including information packets.</li></ul>



<p><strong>About Earth Day Network</strong></p>



<ul><li>EDO is a driving force steering environmental awareness around the world.&nbsp; Our mission is to grow and diversify the environmental movement worldwide, and to mobilize it as the most effective vehicle for promoting a healthy, sustainable planet.&nbsp; We pursue our mission through education, politics, events, and consumer activism.</li><li>EDN offers competitive salary compensation with commensurate with experience and a complete benefits package including paid vacation, sick leave, and retirement benefits.</li><li>Earth Day Network is an Equal Opportunity Employer</li></ul>



<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong><strong></strong></p>



<ul><li>Education:&nbsp;College degree preferred.</li><li>Knowledge:&nbsp;Extensive knowledge of the environmental, conservation, clean energy or related field</li><li>Work Experience:&nbsp;At least three years of foundation, membership and/or individual donor fundraising experience.</li><li>Skills:&nbsp;Excellent written and oral communication skills; strong interpersonal, supervisory strategic planning and training skills; excellent media skills; good computer skills; familiarity with database programs helpful.</li><li>Capabilities:&nbsp;Ability to work well with a wide range of people, work well under pressure, and adapt to changing situations.</li><li>Long hours possible; travel required</li></ul>



<p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p>



<p>Interested and qualified candidates, please forward a cover letter, including salary requirements, and a resume to: <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#3159437154504345595550481f5e4356"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="ff978dbf9a9e8d8b979b9e86d1908d98">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> with “Grants Manager – ‘your full name’ ” in the subject line.</p>



<p><a href="#top">Back to top</a></p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-text-color has-background has-luminous-vivid-amber-background-color has-luminous-vivid-amber-color is-style-wide"/>



<a id="devcoord"></a>



<h2>Development Coordinator</h2>



<p>The Development Coordinator will report to the Director of Foundations and Individual Giving.</p>



<p>Job Overview In partnership with the Director of Foundations and Individual Giving, the Development Coordinator will play a critical role in supporting EARTHDAY.ORG’s development efforts. This opportunity is ideal for someone interested in gaining experience in all facets of nonprofit foundation and Individual giving relationship building and truly making an impact in their day-today.</p>



<p>Responsibilities and Duties</p>



<p>• Work with the Director of Development on creating an annual development calendar to ensure year-round engagement and stewardship of individual and institutional funders</p>



<p>• Assist Director of Development in determining appropriate systems to ensure accurate processing and fulfilling of all donations, the accuracy and management of donor records and files, reporting, and prompt donor acknowledgement</p>



<p>• Help Director of Development to develop, implement, and interpret operating policies and procedures for Development</p>



<p>• Maintain accurate and up-to-date records in database and other files</p>



<p>• Ensure overall data integrity</p>



<p>• Run reports and analyze data to share with the Director of Development</p>



<p>• Generate and track acknowledgement letters</p>



<p>• Monitor external donation portals to ensure prompt acknowledgement</p>



<p>• Ensure the appropriate follow-up occurs with donors</p>



<p>• Help to develop content for communications with donors</p>



<p>• Help with donor outreach</p>



<p>• Remain up to date on industry best practices for stewardship and cultivation</p>



<p>• Perform prospect research to look for new funding opportunities</p>



<p>• Assist in writing proposals and reports</p>



<p>• Other duties as assigned</p>



<p>Qualifications</p>



<p>• Bachelor’s Degree (BA, BS, etc.) and 1-2 years of relevant experience or 4+ years of experience in lieu of degree</p>



<p>• Prior development experience is preferred</p>



<p>• Experience with CRM databases, especially NationBuilder, a plus</p>



<p>• Strong computer skills including Microsoft Office software, especially PowerPoint, Word, and Excel</p>



<p>• Any graphic design experience a plus</p>



<p>• Passionate about the EARTHDAY.ORG mission</p>



<p>• Exceptional interpersonal skills and a commitment to representing EARTHDAY.ORG with enthusiasm, warmth, and professionalism</p>



<p>• Superior tact, discretion, maturity, and judgment in handling highly sensitive, often confidential information</p>



<p>• The ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment and to multitask and manage multiple projects and assignments often with competing deadlines</p>



<p>• Able to work well on a team and individually</p>



<p>• Ability to meet deadlines</p>



<p>• Excellent critical thinking, problem solving, organizational skills, and attention to detail</p>



<p>• Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p>



<p>• Strong editing and proofing skills</p>



<p>• Ability to occasionally work during the weekend or evening</p>



<p>Physical demands and work environment</p>



<p>• This is a sedentary position, in which you may occasionally need to lift and carry books or files up to 10 pounds.</p>



<p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p>



<p>Interested and qualified candidates, please forward a cover letter, including salary requirements, and a resume to: <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#e9819ba98c889b9d818d8890c7869b8e"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="7a12083a1f1b080e121e1b035415081d">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> with “Development Coordinator – ‘your full name’ ” in the subject line.</p>



<p>EARTHDAY.ORG is an Equal Opportunity Employer. EARTHDAY.ORG does not discriminate in employment on the basis of race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy and gender identity), national origin, political affiliation, sexual orientation, marital status, disability status, genetic information, age, membership in an employee organization, retaliation, parental status, military service, or other non-merit factor.</p>



